        "subject": "LU-19443 utils: show help for invalid interactive commands",
        "message": "LU-19443 utils: show help for invalid interactive commands\n\nWhen lctl interactive mode is used, it is possible to type \"help\" to\nprint the short help for a given command. It would be helpful if\ninvalid commands, such as \"?\", also presented the short help of the\ncommand currently being run in interactive mode.\n\nThis patch adds this functionality.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Marc Vef <mvef@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Ie8cb92c5e4f57f18d501dac4525f36788a03f38d\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/61642\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Sebastien Buisson <sbuisson@ddn.com>\n"
